 STATIC-SITE-CSS-IMPORT-DEPTH-LIMIT-FIXTURE-1 [P2 static-site/release-health] scripts/update-site-asset-manifest.js + scripts/static-site-asset-references.test.js: after PR #2467 lands, add a focused negative fixture for recursive CSS `@import` depth limiting so a temp site with more than the maximum allowed local stylesheet import chain fails fast with the explicit CSS import depth error instead of recursing indefinitely or silently dropping later stylesheet asset references; keep normal cycle handling, nested/root-relative import traversal, external/data/CSS-variable ignores, and deterministic manifest output | why: PR #2467 adds `maxStylesheetImportDepth` plus a visited-set cycle guard while testing normal nested imports and a cycle through a back-import, but no fixture forces the depth ceiling. A future refactor could remove the guard or convert it into silent truncation while existing import/cycle fixtures still pass. Duplicate search found site-root, comment, symlink, and style-tag CSS rows, but no dedicated depth-limit negative guard | verify: NODE_OPTIONS="--v8-pool-size=1" node --test scripts/static-site-asset-references.test.js --test-name-pattern "CSS import depth|depth limit|recursive CSS" && npm run typecheck -- --pretty false && git diff --check; fixtures fail if over-deep local `@import` chains do not throw the documented depth error, if normal chains/cycles break, or if current CSS URL extraction regresses
 STATIC-SOURCES-EXTRA-LOCALE-PROVENANCE-COPY-1 [P0 source-provenance/static-i18n] site/i18n-extras.js + scripts/static-site-source-provenance-copy.test.js + scripts/static-site-i18n-extras.test.js + tests/e2e/static-i18n-extras-language-selector.spec.ts: update every extra-locale static Sources and Terms accuracy string (`terms.s3.p`, `sources.lede`, `sources.meta3.v`, `sources.s1.*`, `sources.s4.li1`) so zh-Hans, zh-Hant, ar, ckb, fa, pl, so, ti, tr, and uk describe the shipped UHR + Derived provenance split, current counts, per-question badges, and the UHR-only setting instead of saying the bank is UHR-only or only `Sverige i fokus`; add guards that fail when extra-locale Sources copy lacks Derived/provenance/count language or contains UHR-only current-bank claims | why: focused REVIEWER source-provenance i18n pass on clean `origin/main` found EN/SV `site/app.js` correctly says ~179 UHR-cited and ~716 derived questions, but all 10 extra-locale dictionaries in `site/i18n-extras.js` still render stale UHR-only Sources/Terms copy (`sources.meta3.v: "Sverige i fokus"`, `sources.s4.li1` says the bank is only UHR, and `sources.lede` says other source families are not listed until such questions launch). A direct VM scan reported `localeCount:10`, `offenderCount:10`, with every extra locale missing Derived/count wording and carrying UHR-only claims; focused source/i18n tests still passed 24/24, so current guards cover EN/SV fallback and citation labels but miss learner-visible extra-locale source-provenance drift. Duplicate search found static provenance count and extra-locale legal/purchase/i18n rows, but no live Sources-page provenance row for extra languages | verify: NODE_OPTIONS="--v8-pool-size=1" node --test scripts/static-site-source-provenance-copy.test.js scripts/static-site-i18n-extras.test.js scripts/static-site-source-i18n.test.js --test-name-pattern "Sources|source provenance|extra locale|UHR|Derived|179|716|terms.s3.p|sources.lede|sources.s4" && CI=1 EXPO_NO_TELEMETRY=1 NODE_OPTIONS="--v8-pool-size=1" npm run build:web:export -- --max-workers 2 && CI=1 NODE_OPTIONS="--v8-pool-size=1" npm run test:e2e -- tests/e2e/static-i18n-extras-language-selector.spec.ts --workers=1 --grep "Sources|extra languages|UHR|Derived|provenance" && git diff --check; fixtures fail if any extra locale still says the current bank is only UHR/Sverige i fokus, omits the derived family or current counts, loses the UHR-only setting explanation, or regresses existing extra-locale navigation/root lang/RTL behavior
 PROGRESS-BAR-FOCUSED-PARITY-GATE-1 [P2 release-tests/a11y] scripts/validate-content.js + tests/content-progress-bar-accessibility-parity.test.js + tests/content-test-script-routing.test.js: add a focused `--focus-progress-bar-accessibility` validator path that runs only the shared ProgressBar foundation/adapter parity rules, emits `progressBarAccessibilityRulesExpected`, `progressBarAccessibilityRulesValidated`, and `progressBarAccessibilityParityValidated`, and make the ProgressBar parity test use that focused path while preserving full `npm run validate:content` coverage | why: PR #2470 collapsed the duplicate UI progress-bar implementation into a thin adapter and raised the rule count to 25, but the focused ProgressBar test still shells out to full `scripts/validate-content.js`; local aggregate `test:content` exposed many unrelated stale parity failures, so future ProgressBar regressions should be independently debuggable without being masked by unrelated content drift | verify: NODE_OPTIONS="--v8-pool-size=1" node scripts/validate-content.js --focus-progress-bar-accessibility prints only the ProgressBar accessibility summary with expected/validated counts at 25 and parity true; NODE_OPTIONS="--v8-pool-size=1" node --test tests/content-progress-bar-accessibility-parity.test.js tests/content-test-script-routing.test.js --test-name-pattern "ProgressBar|progress bar|focus-progress-bar|adapter|duplicate" passes; full `npm run validate:content` still includes the same ProgressBar counters; npm run typecheck -- --pretty false; git diff --check
+REMOVE-ADS-ANDROID-PRODUCT-ID-PARITY-1 lib/monetization/purchases.ts + scripts/monetization.test.js + tests/content-remove-ads-purchase-runtime-parity.test.js + scripts/validate-content.js: split Remove Ads store product identifiers by platform so Apple billing keeps `com.billyyiu.swedishcivictest.removeads` while Google Play purchase/restore requests use `removeads`, and make restore/receipt validation accept the matching platform product id without weakening the persisted entitlement record | why: current `publishing/admob-iap-setup-runbook.md` tells the operator to create Google Play IAP product id `removeads`, but `createNativePurchaseProvider` passes `productId` into both `apple.sku` and `google.skus`, `REMOVE_ADS_PRODUCT_ID` is `com.billyyiu.swedishcivictest.removeads`, and the existing monetization/runtime parity tests pass while enforcing that single id, so an Android device would query/restore the wrong Play product | verify: npm run test:monetization && NODE_OPTIONS="--v8-pool-size=1" node --test tests/content-remove-ads-purchase-runtime-parity.test.js && npm run validate:content; add a source or provider-capture guard proving native `requestPurchase` sends Apple sku `com.billyyiu.swedishcivictest.removeads`, Google skus [`removeads`], restore filters Android purchases with productId `removeads`, and the operator runbook product ids match exported constants
